Comment: After spending years and years reading, waiting with anticipation, and thoroughly enjoying each and every Diary of a wimpy Kid book as a child, I am completely and utterly disgusted with this unfunny, boorish, and vexatious, piece of human garbage, that 20th Century Fox dares to call a movie. It is absolutely dreadful, un loyal to the characters, the character's traits, and their appearances. It is difficult to describe the feeling of something that so heavily influenced your childhood life, be turned into a cheaply run waste of Hollywood money and time (that few of which is spent). First ofan Kurt Kobain (hopefully everyone and everything affiliated with this "movie" will have the same fate as him). Why is Greg a prepubescent four year old who can barely say his lines correctly even with this terribly cut trailer, who also looks like he hasn't even touched a bar of soap in two months. And finally the parents and Rowley character look completely cookie cutter in comparison to the original movies that they so desperately tried to imitate. This movie as a whole, looks like the trailer to a new Disney Channel sitcom that gets cancelled three episodes in. I hope that 20th Century Fox ends up loosing more money than Hillary Clinton on her failed campaign. I cannot fully describe the feelings of pure hatred and lack of brain cells that I have experienced as of seeing this monstrosity. Good Day.

Comment: Rodrick no longer fits the description of his character from the book AT ALL, which is why people are so angry about the change of actors. It's completely understandable that they had to cast new actors for Greg and Rowley, since now the originals are too old to play their part. But they should have gotten actors who not only looks like the original characters from the book, but are in the same age range. Having actors that appear under the age of ten don't make good middle schoolers if they look like they just came out of preschool. The parents are fine, I guess, but they should have casted a new mom. Mom never even looked like herself from the old movie, the original mom has short black hair. Lastly, this movie is going to be a gigantic waste of money and time. Not only are people angry at the entirety of the film itself, but literally no one even asked for this movie. Even so, they still should have been more smart with choosing the right actors... this is an abomination.

Comment: After spending years and years reading, waiting with anticipation, and thoroughly enjoying each and every Diary of a wimpy Kid book as a child, I am completely and utterly disgusted with this unfunny, boorish, and vexatious, piece of human garbage, that 20th Century Fox dares to call a movie. It is absolutely dreadful, un loyal to the characters, the character's traits, and their appearances. It is difficult to describe the feeling of something that so heavily influenced your childhood life, be turned into a cheaply run waste of Hollywood money and time (that few of which is spent). First of all, why does Rodricks character look like an Asian Kurt Kobain (hopefully everyone and everything affiliated with this "movie" will have the same fate as him). Why is Greg a prepubescent four year old who can barely say his lines correctly even with this terribly cut trailer, who also looks like he hasn't even touched a bar of soap in two months. And finally the parents and Rowley character look completely cookie cutter in comparison to the original movies that they so desperately tried to imitate. This movie as a whole, looks like the trailer to a new Disney Channel sitcom that gets cancelled three episodes in. I hope that 20th Century Fox ends up loosing more money than Hillary Clinton on her failed campaign. I cannot fully describe the feelings of pure hatred and lack of brain cells that I have experienced as of seeing this monstrosity. Good Day.
